nncExtBasics.name: nncExtBasics
nncExtBasics.contactinfo: Newbridge Networks Corporation Postal: 600 March Road Kanata, Ontario Canada K2K 2E6 Phone: +1 613 591 3600 Fax: +1 613 591 3680
nncExtBasics.description: The MIB module containing management information for basic network element functions: restart info, environmental info, box identity, etc.

Nci2DeviceIDType.name: Nci2DeviceIDType
Nci2DeviceIDType.description: An entities device identifier. These numbers are assigned by the device ID administrator. He/she must be contacted if new device IDs need to be added.

CurrentGenericType.name: CurrentGenericType
CurrentGenericType.description: The revision of the current executing firmware in the standard Newbridge fashion. The identifier is a string of up to 12 ASCII characters of the form ZAABCD-TM-LL where: ZAABC identifies the product, D identifies the major release T identifies the load type M identifies the minor release and LL identifies the load number

ProductPartNumberType.name: ProductPartNumberType
ProductPartNumberType.description: This type defines the standard Newbridge assembly part number. The assembly number identifier is a string of 17 ASCII characters of the form 90-xxxx-VV-CC-MMM where: 90 - Marketing part number xxxx - sequence number VV - Variant CC - Customer Code MMM - Manufacturing Code

CardIDType.name: CardIDType
CardIDType.description: An module identifier (from GNI0001 found in Tech Lib).

CardSerialNumberType.name: CardSerialNumberType
CardSerialNumberType.description: An module serial number specification. 2d-2d,1d,8d field bytes contents range ----- ----- -------- ----- 1 1-2 week 1..52 2 3-4 year 0..99 3 5 assembly line 0..9 4 6-10 assembly number 0..99999

NncSwStatus.name: NncSwStatus
NncSwStatus.description: The NncSwStatus represents the status of any software bank.

NncSwBank.name: NncSwBank
NncSwBank.description: The NncSwBank represents a software bank.

nncExtSysProductName.name: nncExtSysProductName
nncExtSysProductName.description: The marketing name for the product, e.g. 8231 MainStreet

nncExtSysCurrentGeneric.name: nncExtSysCurrentGeneric
nncExtSysCurrentGeneric.description: The revision of the current executing firmware in the controlling component of the system.

nncExtSysProductPartNumber.name: nncExtSysProductPartNumber
nncExtSysProductPartNumber.description: The Newbridge assembly part number for the given system.

nncExtSysNci2DeviceID.name: nncExtSysNci2DeviceID
nncExtSysNci2DeviceID.description: The NCI2 device ID assigned to the device.

nncExtSysCurrentDateAndTime.name: nncExtSysCurrentDateAndTime
nncExtSysCurrentDateAndTime.description: If set on the device, this returns the date and time. Otherwise, returns all 0s.

nncExtSysCardTable.name: nncExtSysCardTable
nncExtSysCardTable.description: Table containing information about the card in this system.

nncExtSysCardEntry.name: nncExtSysCardEntry
nncExtSysCardEntry.description: An entry in the system card table.

nncExtSysCardName.name: nncExtSysCardName
nncExtSysCardName.description: The name of the card as saved on the SEEP.

nncExtSysCardSerialNumber.name: nncExtSysCardSerialNumber
nncExtSysCardSerialNumber.description: Serial number of the current card.

nncExtEnvFanStatus.name: nncExtEnvFanStatus
nncExtEnvFanStatus.description: The current status of the fan. This is product dependent.

nncExtEnvTemperatureSensor.name: nncExtEnvTemperatureSensor
nncExtEnvTemperatureSensor.description: The suitability of the current temperature. This is product dependent.

nncExtEnvPlus12Status.name: nncExtEnvPlus12Status
nncExtEnvPlus12Status.description: Whether or not the +12V rail is in spec. This is product dependent.

nncExtEnvMinus12Status.name: nncExtEnvMinus12Status
nncExtEnvMinus12Status.description: Whether or not the -12V rail is in spec. This is product dependent.

FanStatusType.name: FanStatusType
FanStatusType.description: A value of this type identifies if the fan status is ok or bad

nncExtEnvFanTable.name: nncExtEnvFanTable
nncExtEnvFanTable.description: This table holds the fan status information

nncExtEnvFanIndex.name: nncExtEnvFanIndex
nncExtEnvFanIndex.description: The index into the fan table

nncExtEnvFanStatusByFanIndex.name: nncExtEnvFanStatusByFanIndex
nncExtEnvFanStatusByFanIndex.description: The state of the fan - ok or bad

PwrSupplyStatusType.name: PwrSupplyStatusType
PwrSupplyStatusType.description: A value of this type identifies the power supply status

nncExtEnvPwrSupplyTable.name: nncExtEnvPwrSupplyTable
nncExtEnvPwrSupplyTable.description: This table holds the fan status information

nncExtEnvPwrSupplySlotIndex.name: nncExtEnvPwrSupplySlotIndex
nncExtEnvPwrSupplySlotIndex.description: Power Supply Slot Number - Ranges from 1 to 255

nncExtEnvPwrSupplyStatus.name: nncExtEnvPwrSupplyStatus
nncExtEnvPwrSupplyStatus.description: The state of the power supply - ok , off, bad or not present

nncExtRestarts.name: nncExtRestarts
nncExtRestarts.description: The number of times the active code bank has restarted.

nncExtFaultInducedRestarts.name: nncExtFaultInducedRestarts
nncExtFaultInducedRestarts.description: The number of restarts of the active code bank that have been caused by a fault, e.g. processor trap.

nncExtLastFault.name: nncExtLastFault
nncExtLastFault.description: The cause of the last restart of the active code bank that was caused by a fault, e.g. processor trap.

nncExtFaultRepetitions.name: nncExtFaultRepetitions
nncExtFaultRepetitions.description: The number of consecutive times the fault reported in nncExtLastFault has been repeated.

nncExtRestartTracebackTable.name: nncExtRestartTracebackTable
nncExtRestartTracebackTable.description: The sequence of program counter values that lead to the last recorded fault.

nncExtRestartTracebackEntry.name: nncExtRestartTracebackEntry
nncExtRestartTracebackEntry.description: An entry in the sequence of program counter values.

nncExtRestartTracebackIndex.name: nncExtRestartTracebackIndex
nncExtRestartTracebackIndex.description: The index into the traceback table

nncExtRestartTracebackPCValue.name: nncExtRestartTracebackPCValue
nncExtRestartTracebackPCValue.description: The program counter value for this entry in the traceback table.

nncExtRestartRegisterTable.name: nncExtRestartRegisterTable
nncExtRestartRegisterTable.description: The sequence of register values at the last recorded fault.

nncExtRestartRegisterEntry.name: nncExtRestartRegisterEntry
nncExtRestartRegisterEntry.description: An entry in the set of register values.

nncExtRestartRegisterIndex.name: nncExtRestartRegisterIndex
nncExtRestartRegisterIndex.description: The index into the Register table. The Index to register mapping for a Motorola processor is as follows: 1 - D0 2 - D1 : 8 - D8 9 - A0 : 15 - A6 16 - Status Reg 17 - Program Counter

nncExtRestartRegisterValue.name: nncExtRestartRegisterValue
nncExtRestartRegisterValue.description: The register value for this entry in the Register table.

nncExtRestartForceToBoot.name: nncExtRestartForceToBoot
nncExtRestartForceToBoot.description: A set will cause the box to start executing from the boot PROM after the delay specified by the value written. A second set before the delay has expired will be rejected with badValue. A read will return zero.

nncExtRestartCause.name: nncExtRestartCause
nncExtRestartCause.description: The cause of the last restart of the system.

nncExtRestartSystem.name: nncExtRestartSystem
nncExtRestartSystem.description: A set will cause the Node to restart after a specified delay and then execute the System code that resides in the Next Active Code Bank. The delay is specified by the value written. A second set before the delay has expired will be rejected with badValue. A read will return zero.

nncExtCodeSpaceCurrentlyActive.name: nncExtCodeSpaceCurrentlyActive
nncExtCodeSpaceCurrentlyActive.description: The index into the code space table of the code space from which the box is currently executing

nncExtCodeSpaceNextActive.name: nncExtCodeSpaceNextActive
nncExtCodeSpaceNextActive.description: The index into the code space table of the code space from which the box will execute after the next restart.

nncExtCodeSpaceNumber.name: nncExtCodeSpaceNumber
nncExtCodeSpaceNumber.description: The number of code spaces supported by this box.

nncExtCodeSpaceTable.name: nncExtCodeSpaceTable
nncExtCodeSpaceTable.description: Information about all of the code spaces present in this box.

nncExtCodeSpaceEntry.name: nncExtCodeSpaceEntry
nncExtCodeSpaceEntry.description: Information about one of the code spaces present in this box.

nncExtCodeSpaceSize.name: nncExtCodeSpaceSize
nncExtCodeSpaceSize.description: The size (in bytes) of the maximum code space available in flash memory.

nncExtCodeSpaceStatus.name: nncExtCodeSpaceStatus
nncExtCodeSpaceStatus.description: Whether or not the specified code space is considered to be sane e.g.,checksum is valid.

nncExtCodeSpaceGeneric.name: nncExtCodeSpaceGeneric
nncExtCodeSpaceGeneric.description: Which generic is contained in the code space.

nncExtCodeSpaceDownloadDate.name: nncExtCodeSpaceDownloadDate
nncExtCodeSpaceDownloadDate.description: The date on which this generic was downloaded. This OBJECT is known by the target.

nncExtCodeSpaceDownloadTime.name: nncExtCodeSpaceDownloadTime
nncExtCodeSpaceDownloadTime.description: The time at which this generic was downloaded. This OBJECT is known by the target.

nncExtCodeSpaceDownloadServer.name: nncExtCodeSpaceDownloadServer
nncExtCodeSpaceDownloadServer.description: The address of the source of the generic that is present in the code space.

nncExtCodeSpaceDownloadRequestor.name: nncExtCodeSpaceDownloadRequestor
nncExtCodeSpaceDownloadRequestor.description: The address of the entity that caused this code space to be downloaded with the current generic.

nncExtCodeSpaceCompressionType.name: nncExtCodeSpaceCompressionType
nncExtCodeSpaceCompressionType.description: The kind of compression used on the load before it was placed into flash.

nncExtCodeSpaceLoadSize.name: nncExtCodeSpaceLoadSize
nncExtCodeSpaceLoadSize.description: The size (in bytes) of the load stored in this code space when decompressed.

nncExtCodeSpaceCompressLoadSize.name: nncExtCodeSpaceCompressLoadSize
nncExtCodeSpaceCompressLoadSize.description: The size (in bytes) of the load stored in this code space when compressed.

nncExtNVMUsageTable.name: nncExtNVMUsageTable
nncExtNVMUsageTable.description: How much NVM is used in the box in bytes.

nncExtNVMUsageEntry.name: nncExtNVMUsageEntry
nncExtNVMUsageEntry.description: How much NVM is used in a pool of it

nncExtNVMPoolSize.name: nncExtNVMPoolSize
nncExtNVMPoolSize.description: The total number of bytes in the pool

nncExtNVMPoolBytesUsed.name: nncExtNVMPoolBytesUsed
nncExtNVMPoolBytesUsed.description: The number of bytes used in the pool

nncExtNVMLastRepair.name: nncExtNVMLastRepair
nncExtNVMLastRepair.description: Details of the last repair made to the database returned in a string format -- a readable form of the following: Offset Length Meaning 0 1 Number Of Bytes in the String (=31) 1 1 Length of repaired item (in bytes) 2 4 Address of Block containing repaired item 6 2 block number of the repaired block 8 2 item number of repaired entry 10 2 first parameter of repaired item 12 2 second parameter of repaired item 14 1 length of date string 15 9 date of repair (DD-MMM-YY) 24 1 length of time string (=6) 25 6 time of repair (HH:MMX)

nncExtProbeMPLTable.name: nncExtProbeMPLTable
nncExtProbeMPLTable.description: A window into the Master Parameter List.

nncExtProbeMPLEntry.name: nncExtProbeMPLEntry
nncExtProbeMPLEntry.description: An entry in the master parameter list. The instance identifer is of the form: nncExtProbeMPL.<c>.<i>.<m1>.<m2>.<m3>.<m4>

nncExtProbeMPL.name: nncExtProbeMPL
nncExtProbeMPL.description: A window into in the Master Parameter List. The instance identifer is of the form: <c>.<i>.<m1>.<m2>.<m3>.<m4>

SvcEpdOptionType.name: SvcEpdOptionType
SvcEpdOptionType.description: A value of this type identifies the early packet discard option - off or on

SvcPpdOptionType.name: SvcPpdOptionType
SvcPpdOptionType.description: A value of this type identifies the partial packet discard option - off or on

nncDiagUndoAll.name: nncDiagUndoAll
nncDiagUndoAll.description: A write of 'undo' to this parameter will cause all maintenance operations to be removed, e.g. loopbacks busy-outs, etc

nncExtStartupDiagnosticResults.name: nncExtStartupDiagnosticResults
nncExtStartupDiagnosticResults.description: If ALL of the systems startup diagnostic tests passed successfully, then this object is set to passed otherwise it is set to failed
